metadata.title: Piper J-3 Cub
aws::graph::propositions: Piper J-3 Cub Variants and Certifications
J3L is a variant of the Piper J-3 Cub.
J3L was certified on 17 September 1938.
J3L is equipped with a Lycoming O-145-A1 engine of 50 horsepower (37 kilowatts).
J3L can alternatively be equipped with a Lycoming O-145-A2 engine of 55 horsepower (41 kilowatts).
J3L can alternatively be equipped with a Lycoming O-145-A3 engine of 55 horsepower (41 kilowatts).
J3L-S is a variant of the Piper J-3 Cub.
J3L-S was certified on 2 May 1939.
J3L-S is equipped with a Lycoming O-145-A1 engine of 50 horsepower (37 kilowatts).
J3L-S can alternatively be equipped with a Lycoming O-145-A2 engine of 55 horsepower (41 kilowatts).
J3L-S can alternatively be equipped with a Lycoming O-145-A3 engine of 55 horsepower (41 kilowatts).
J3L-S is equipped with an optional float kit.
J3L-65 is a variant of the Piper J-3 Cub.
J3L-65 was certified on 27 May 1940.
J3L-65 is equipped with a Lycoming O-145-B1 engine of 65 horsepower (48 kilowatts).
J3L-65 can alternatively be equipped with a Lycoming O-145-B2 engine of 65 horsepower (48 kilowatts).
J3L-65 can alternatively be equipped with a Lycoming O-145-B3 engine of 65 horsepower (48 kilowatts).
J3L-65S is a variant of the Piper J-3 Cub.
J3L-65S was certified on 27 May 1940.
J3L-65S is equipped with a Lycoming O-145-B1 engine of 65 horsepower (48 kilowatts).
J3L-65S can alternatively be equipped with a Lycoming O-145-B2 engine of 65 horsepower (48 kilowatts).
J3L-65S can alternatively be equipped with a Lycoming O-145-B3 engine of 65 horsepower (48 kilowatts).
J3L-65S is equipped with an optional float kit.
